From: 3090 team <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: 2026-06-10
Subject: [PATCH] gemma4_unified video processor: count soft tokens across ALL frames

Fixes A1-V (sprint LOG 2026-06-10): the first video request to the 12B
killed the scheduler with `split_with_sizes expects sum 768 ... got [64]`.
The vendored video processor (patch 046, verbatim from transformers main)
declares num_soft_tokens_per_video = merged_patches.shape[1] — the
PER-FRAME merged-patch count — while the unified model's _embed_patches
emits every frame's non-padding patches (num_frames x per_frame; the 26B
12-frame validator video = 12 x 64 = 768). __call__ therefore expanded 64
placeholder tokens against 768 embeddings. Declare the all-frames total;
per-frame -1 padding is still dropped model-side. Verified live: video
probe crash -> PASS, 12B goes 4/5 -> 5/5 capabilities.
Upstream note: transformers main may carry the same defect (vendor was
verbatim 2026-06-07) — report there, not sglang.

diff --git a/python/sglang/srt/configs/video_processing_gemma4_unified.py b/python/sglang/srt/configs/video_processing_gemma4_unified.py
index 0c4818caf..fa2141cb0 100644
--- a/python/sglang/srt/configs/video_processing_gemma4_unified.py
+++ b/python/sglang/srt/configs/video_processing_gemma4_unified.py
@@ -326,21 +326,27 @@ class Gemma4UnifiedVideoProcessor(BaseVideoProcessor):
                 indexing="xy",
             )
             stacked_grid = torch.stack(patch_grid, dim=-1)
             teacher_positions = stacked_grid.reshape(patches.shape[1], 2)
             teacher_positions = teacher_positions[None, ...].repeat(num_frames, 1, 1)
 
             # Step 5: Merge k×k teacher patches into model patches via patches_merge
             # (num_frames, num_teacher_patches, 768) → (num_frames, num_model_patches, 6912)
             num_model_patches = patches.shape[1] // (pooling_kernel_size**2)
             merged_patches, merged_positions = patches_merge(patches, teacher_positions, num_model_patches)
-            num_soft_tokens_per_video.append(merged_patches.shape[1])
+            # [3090 050] total across ALL frames: the unified model embeds every
+            # frame's merged non-padding patches — (num_frames, per_frame, ...) —
+            # but this declared only shape[1] (ONE frame). The undercount made
+            # __call__ expand 64 placeholders for a 12-frame video whose embedder
+            # emits 12*64=768 -> split_with_sizes scheduler crash on the first
+            # video request (A1-V, sprint LOG 2026-06-10).
+            num_soft_tokens_per_video.append(int(merged_patches.shape[0] * merged_patches.shape[1]))
 
             # Step 6: Pad merged patches and positions to max_soft_tokens
             merged_patches, merged_positions = pad_to_max_patches(merged_patches, merged_positions, max_soft_tokens)
             pixel_values.append(merged_patches)
             position_ids.append(merged_positions)
 
         # Stack into batch tensors
         pixel_values = torch.stack(pixel_values, dim=0)
         position_ids = torch.stack(position_ids, dim=0)
 
